revision.text:
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2017}}
'''Academy of Science Fiction, Fantasy and Horror Films''' is an [[United States of America|American]] non-profit organization established in 1972 and dedicated to the advancement of [[science fiction]], [[fantasy]], and [[Horror fiction|horror]] in [[film]], [[television]], and [[home video]]. The Academy is headquartered in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] and was founded by Dr. Donald A. Reed.
The Academy distributes its [[Saturn Award]]s annually to the best films of the genres. The award was initially and is still sometimes loosely referred to as a Golden Scroll. The Academy also publishes ''Saturn Rings,'' its official organ.
==See also== *[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]]
