{{Infobox person | name = Brooke Kennedy | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | othername = | birth_date = <!--{{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = | occupation = Television producer | years_active = 1979–present | spouse = | website = }}
'''Brooke Kennedy''' is an American television producer and director. Her credits include ''[[Crime Story (TV series)|Crime Story]]'', ''[[My So-Called Life]]'', ''[[Numbers (TV series)|Numb3rs]]'', ''[[Pushing Daisies]]'' and ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.studentpressreview.com/october-2009-issue/2009-sjw |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130815124711/http://www.studentpressreview.com/october-2009-issue/2009-sjw |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-08-15 |title=• 2009 Summer Journalism Workshop : SPR |publisher=Student Press Review |date= |accessdate=2013-08-15 }}</ref> She was also a producer and director on ''[[Third Watch]]'' and currently serves as a producer on ''[[The Good Wife]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dga.org/Craft/DGAQ/All-Articles/1302-Spring-2013/The-Good-Wife.aspx |title=Order in the Court |publisher=Dga.org |date= |accessdate=2013-08-15}}</ref> In addition, she was also a writer on the series ''Prince Street'' and ''Third Watch''. In 2010 and 2011, she was nominated two [[Primetime Emmy Awards]] for ''The Good Wife'' as a part of the producing team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emmys.com/award_history_search?person=Brooke+Kennedy&program=&start_year=1949&end_year=2013&network=All&web_category=All&winner=All |title=Primetime Emmy® Award Database |publisher=Emmys.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-15}}</ref>
