{{italic title}} {{no footnotes|date=October 2018}}
[[File:Tiziano,_san_girolamo_penitente.jpg|thumb|300px]] '''''Saint Jerome in Penitence''''' or '''''Penitent Saint Jerome''''' is a c.1531 oil on canvas painting [[Titian]], now in the [[Louvre]] in Paris. It is first mentioned in the collections of [[Louis XIV]] and may have come from the [[Gonzaga collection]], perhaps making it the ''Saint Jerome'' mentioned in [[Federico II Gonzaga, Duke of Mantua|Federico Gonzaga]]'s correspondence, which can be dated to 1531. A second theory argues that the work was intended for Federico's mother [[Isabella d'Este]], who wanted a nocturnal scene.
==Sources== *{{it icon}} Francesco Valcanover, ''L'opera completa di Tiziano'', Rizzoli, Milano 1969.
==External links== *[http://cartelen.louvre.fr/cartelen/visite?srv=car_not_frame&idNotice=22883&langue=fr Louvre website]
